<headline>Special Weather Statement issued April 17 at 2:43PM CDT  by NWS Memphis</headline>
<description>...A strong thunderstorm will impact portions of southwestern
Lafayette, northwestern Yalobusha and southern Panola Counties
through 315 PM CDT...
At 243 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Batesville, moving east at 30 mph.
HAZARD...Pea size hail.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Minor damage to outdoor objects is possible.
Locations impacted include...
Batesville, Pope, Burgess, Courtland, Shuford, Asa, Eureka Springs
and Chapeltown.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.25 IN
MAX WIND GUST...&lt;30 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
